name: WIN10-114
description: Proof of concept for a bug, that allows any user to crash the Windows Event Log service of any other Windows 10/Windows Server 2022 machine on the same domain. The crash occurs in wevtsvc!VerifyUnicodeString when an attacker sends a malformed UNICODE_STRING object to the ElfrRegisterEventSourceW method exposed by the RPC-based EventLog Remoting Protocol.
evidence: Windows 10 is vulnerable to the Event-Log-Crasher
